  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Boil a full kettle</p><p>Add your <strong>sausages</strong> to a baking tray (use <strong>tin foil</strong> to avoid mess!)</p><p>Put the tray in the oven for 20-25 min or until the sausages are cooked through (no pink meat!)</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1680084069932-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1680084069932-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1680084069932-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1680084069932-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1680084069932-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the sausages are in the oven, add your <strong>waxy potatoes</strong> to a pot of plenty of <strong>boiled water </strong>and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, cook for 17-18 min or until fork-tender</p><p>Once the potatoes are fork tender, drain then return them to the pot and crush gently</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1680084072251-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1680084072251-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1680084072251-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1680084072251-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1680084072251-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Crush your <strong>garlic </strong>open by squashing them with the side of a knife and discard the skins</p><p>Chop your <strong>Italian hard cheese</strong> into small bite-size pieces</p><p>Add your <strong>blanched peas</strong> to a colander and pour <strong>boiled water</strong> all over them to refresh them</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1680084074972-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1680084074972-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1680084074972-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1680084074972-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1680084074972-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>crushed garlic</strong>, <strong>chopped Italian hard cheese</strong>, <strong>flaked almonds </strong>and <strong>half</strong> the<strong> refreshed peas</strong> (you'll use the rest later!) to a <strong>food processor</strong></p><p>Add 2 tbsp<span class=\"text-purple\"> [3 tbsp]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [4 tbsp] </span><strong>olive oil</strong>, <strong>half</strong> your <strong>white wine vinegar</strong> (save the rest for later!) and<strong> </strong>2 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tbsp]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [4 tbsp]</span><strong> cold water</strong> with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong>, then blitz until a coarse paste remains<strong> </strong>– this is your <strong>pea pesto</strong></p><p>Tip: No food processor? Chop everything up as finely as you can and mix it together!</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
